      "body": "I noticed that the headers were updated when a new peer\n  connected. Looking at the debug log:\n\n```\n2026-03-27T15:13:39Z UpdateTip: new best=0000000000000000001337d08cd96b5f708fb1e98d907d5da6f06b42939d6b8f height=634603 version=0x20400000 log2_work=92.029680 tx=538755975 date='2020-06-13T21:17:11Z' progress=0.404176 cache=205.0MiB(1491437txo)\n2026-03-27T15:13:39Z Loading 0 mempool transactions from file...\n2026-03-27T15:13:39Z Imported mempool transactions from file: 0 succeeded, 0 failed, 0 expired, 0 already there, 0 waiting for initial broadcast\n2026-03-27T15:13:39Z initload thread exit\n2026-03-27T15:13:39Z New outbound-full-relay v2 peer connected: version: 70016, blocks=77225, peer=97\n2026-03-27T15:13:39Z New block-relay-only v2 peer connected: version: 70016, blocks=942482, peer=99\n2026-03-27T15:13:39Z Synchronizing blockheaders, height: 942482 (~100.00%)\n2026-03-27T15:13:40Z New block-relay-only v2 peer connected: version: 70016, blocks=941347, peer=100\n2026-03-27T15:13:41Z UpdateTip: new best=00000000000000000001c368b208bb4614a3359cd44a0d47e5574e7c8d0be923 height=634604 version=0x20000000 log2_work=92.029697 tx=53875674\n```\n\n  Once initload finished a new peer is added and it triggered a getheaders request, which fix the GUI info\n\n<img width=\"611\" height=\"323\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f97461a5-d00a-4fd1-b839-9bc804ef645f\" />\n\n",
